# Vite / Vitest build + test cache (written when running vite/vitest from the repo root).
.vite/

# Forensic evidence output — never commit captured screenshots / case data.
# The companion writes here when DFIR_CASES_ROOT points outside companion/
# (e.g. the default-ish ../cases). Keep it out of git.
/cases/

# Server + per-case session logs (DFIR_LOG_LEVEL). Written beside the cases root; may
# carry case identifiers / activity traces — keep out of git like the evidence above.
/logs/
logs/

# Notification channel config (issue #58) — holds webhook URLs + SMTP passwords. Written
# beside the cases root; never commit.
/notifications/
notifications/

# Velociraptor client inventory (issue #70) — holds the fleet's real hostnames/FQDNs/IPs.
# ANCHORED only (a bare `velociraptor/` would also match the src/integrations/velociraptor/ source dir).
/velociraptor/

# CISA KEV catalog cache (issue #99) — downloaded/imported by the analyst at runtime; never commit.
# Anchored to companion/ because casesRoot defaults to companion/cases, so dirname(casesRoot)=companion/.
/kev/
companion/kev/

# Update-check cache (issue #127) — last GitHub release check + the opt-in toggle; runtime state, never commit.
/updates/
companion/updates/

# Secrets / local config
**/.env

# Node
node_modules/
dist/
*.timestamp-*.mjs
.gstack/

# Node SEA build outputs (single-executable Windows EXE staging).
build-sea/
dist-sea/

# Linux AppImage build outputs (issue #127) — AppDir staging + the produced .AppImage + appimagetool.
build-appimage/
dist-appimage/

# Chocolatey package staging (issue #137) — templated nuspec/tools + the produced .nupkg.
dist-choco/

# Docker: the pre-built browser add-on the companion container copies out for "Load unpacked".
/addon/

# Atomic-write temp files. atomicWrite.ts writes `<target>.tmp` then renames it over
# the target; formatters (Prettier-style write-file-atomic) write `<src>.tmp.<pid>.<hex>`.
# In a Dropbox/OneDrive-synced tree a sync/AV lock can orphan one mid-rename — keep these
# out of git so `git add -A` never sweeps them in.
*.tmp
*.tmp.*

# Local planning / process scratch (not part of the shipped project)
.planning/
docs/superpowers/

# Local exports/backups (e.g. GitHub issues/PR snapshots) — not part of the shipped project.
docs/backups/

# Claude Code local tooling / config (per-machine, not part of the shipped project)
.claude/
/CLAUDE.md
